    "body": "@roschler No worries! \r\n\r\n`truffle-develop` is located in [truffle-core](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle-core) and much of its logic is [here](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle-core/blob/develop/lib/repl.js). \r\n\r\nAnother command you might want to check out is [truffle exec](http://truffleframework.com/docs/advanced/commands#exec) which lets you run an arbitrary script in a context that has `web3` and the `artifacts` module injected into it.  It's not interactive but it can be good for writing little routines and seeing the outcome. \r\n\r\n```\r\ntruffle exec <script.js> [--network <name>]\r\n```",
